Package edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.course

Class Activity

java.lang.Object
edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.course.Activity
All Implemented Interfaces:
Conflict
Direct Known Subclasses:
Course
public abstract class Activity
extends java.lang.Object
implements Conflict
Activity is an abstract class that stores information on an activity's title, meeting days, start time, and end time. Serves as a parent class to Course. Provides the abstract methods getShortDisplayArray, getLongDisplayArray, and isDuplicate for subclasses to implement. Implements Conflict interface and its checkConflict abstract method. Checks if two activity instances have at least one day and time that may cause a conflict in a student's schedule.
Author:
Jongwoo Shin

      meetingDays - an activity's meeting days

    • getMeetingString

      public java.lang.String getMeetingString()
      Returns meeting days and meeting times in standard time format for an Activity object. If the meeting days for the activity is arranged, the string "Arranged" will be returned. Implements the helper method getTimeString to convert military time into standard time format in the form of a String.
      Returns:
      the meeting days and times in standard time format. If arranged, just returns "Arranged"

    • checkConflict

      public void checkConflict​(Activity possibleConflictingActivity) throws ConflictException
      Compares the current instance of Activity with possibleConflictingActivity to see if any conflict exists in their days and times. There is a conflict if there is at least one day with an overlapping time, down to the minutes. Nothing happens if there are no conflicts. ConflictExceptin is thrown if a conflict is found.
      Specified by:
      checkConflict in interface Conflict
      Parameters:
      possibleConflictingActivity - the activity that may cause a conflict
      Throws:
      ConflictException - if there is at least one day with an overlapping time
